for python:
    def test(i):
        print(i)
        test(i+1)
    test(0)
    // final output 998

for C++:
    void test(i) {
        cout << i << endl;
        test(i+1);
    }
    test(0);
    // final output 64893

C++ is ridiculously more endurable than python
When facing stack overflow in python (i.e DFS), just switch to C++
